@REM ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~  CONTENTS     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@NODE "HTML_TAGS" "List of supported HTML tags"

    @{B}List of supported HTML tags@{UB}
    ---------------------------

    The program recognizes blocks enclosed between the <XMP> and <LISTING>
    tags, and doesn't interpret the HTML code contained therein.

    Here follows a list of recognized tags, sorted by groups:


    @{B}HTML 2.0@{UB}

    <BASE HREF="">
    <A HREF="">
    <LINK HREF="">
    <IMG SRC="">
    <INPUT SRC="">


    @{B}HTML 3.2@{UB}

    HTML 3.2 inherits all 2.0 tags and adds:

    <BODY BACKGROUND="">
    <APPLET CODEBASE="" CODE="">
    <SCRIPT SRC="">
    <AREA HREF="">


    @{B}HTML 4.0@{UB}

    HTML 4.0 inherits all 3.2 tags and adds:

    <IMG LONGDESC="">
    <APPLET OBJECT="" ARCHIVE="">
    <OBJECT CODEBASE="" DATA="" CLASSID="" ARCHIVE="">
    <FRAME SRC="" LONGDESC="">
    <IFRAME SRC="" LONGDESC="">
    <SCRIPT SRC="">
    <BLOCKQUOTE CITE="">
    <Q CITE="">
    <DEL CITE="">
    <INS CITE="">


    @{B}HTML extensions@{UB}

    The extensions are added to the choosen HTML subset. Netscape and
    Internet Explorer extensions only have some meaning when used with HTML
    3.2 or 4.0.

    @{U}Netscape extensions@{UU}:

    <IMG LOWSRC="">
    <APPLET OBJECT="">
    <OBJECT CODEBASE="" DATA="" CLASSID="" ARCHIVE="" CODE="">
    <EMBED SRC="" PLUGINPAGE="" PLUGINURL="">
    <FRAME SRC="">
    <LAYER SRC="" BACKGROUND="">
    <ILAYER SRC="" BACKGROUND="">
    <SCRIPT SRC="">

    @{U}Internet Explorer extensions@{UU}:

    <IMG LOWSRC="" DYNSRC="">
    <APPLET SRC="">
    <OBJECT CODEBASE="" DATA="" CLASSID="" CODE="">
    <EMBED SRC="">
    <FRAME SRC="">
    <IFRAME SRC="">
    <INPUT SRC="" DYNSRC="" LOWSRC="">
    <SCRIPT SRC="">
    <TABLE BACKGROUD="">
    <BGSOUND SRC="">

    @{U}Other extensions@{UU}:

    <IMG HREF="">
    <FIG SRC="">
    <OVERLAY SRC="">


    @{B}Image-inclusion tags@{UB}:

    <IMG HREF="" SRC="" LONGDESC="" LOWSRC="" DYNSRC="">
    <INPUT SRC="" DYNSRC="" LOWSRC="">


    @{B}Background-inclusion tags@{UB}:

    <BODY BACKGROUND="">
    <TABLE BACKGROUND="">


    @{B}Applet-inclusion tags@{UB}:

    <APPLET CODEBASE="" CODE="" OBJECT="" ARCHIVE="" SRC="">


    @{B}Object-inclusion tags@{UB}:

    <OBJECT CODEBASE="" DATA="" CLASSID="" ARCHIVE="" CODE="">


    For an exhaustive description of the meaning of all supported tags
    you're invited to check the HTML resources mentioned in the
    @{"bibliography" link "RFC"}.

@ENDNODE
